Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for computing multiway cuts in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various fields such as network design and image segmentation. The paper also introduces a new combinatorial result related to vertex separators, which is of interest to researchers in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves some complexity analysis and combinatorial optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
